<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7576> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7576" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator? 44-43. The Octavius Balbus who was proscribed and put to death in 43 (Val. Max. 5.7.3; App. BC 4.21) probably was the C. Octavius who joined the tyrannicides on the Capitol (Plul. Caes. 67.2). See Wiseman, CQ 14, 1964, 124.\n" .
